// The INSTALLED-mods catalog: every mod the build ships, in LOAD order (base
// first, so mods overlay it). This is the wasm-safe index the mods menu lists and
// the loader loads - never a directory scan. Which entries are ENABLED is a runtime
// concern (EnabledMods, persisted separately), NOT baked in here.
//
// Each entry: id (enable key + overlay namespace), name/description (shown in the
// menu), bundle (the mod's `*.bundle.ron`, asset-root-relative), base (true = the
// base game: enabled by default, locked on in the UI).
(mods: [
    (
        id: "base",
        name: "Base Game",
        description: "Nova Protocol - the core sections, ships and scenarios.",
        bundle: "base/base.bundle.ron",
        base: true,
    ),
    (
        id: "demo",
        name: "Demo Mod",
        description: "Example mod: up-armors a hull section and adds an arena scenario.",
        bundle: "mods/demo/demo.bundle.ron",
    ),
])
